  "text": "The Kubernetes API server authentication system is implemented across multiple Go source files organized in a hierarchical architecture. The central orchestration point is `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go`, which contains the `Config` struct and its `New()` method that constructs the complete authentication chain for the API server.\n\nThe authentication chain construction in `config.go:100-236` builds authenticators in the following order:\n1. Front proxy/request header authentication via `headerrequest.NewDynamicVerifyOptionsSecure()` (lines 108-118)\n2. Client certificate (X.509) authentication via `x509.NewDynamic()` (lines 121-124)\n3. Bearer token authentication chain combining:\n   - Token file authenticator from `tokenfile.NewCSV()` (lines 127-133)\n   - Legacy service account tokens via `newLegacyServiceAccountAuthenticator()` (lines 134-140)\n   - Modern service account tokens via `newServiceAccountAuthenticator()` (lines 141-147)\n   - Bootstrap tokens (lines 149-151)\n   - JWT authenticators via `newJWTAuthenticator()` (lines 160-180)\n   - Webhook token authenticator via `newWebhookTokenAuthenticator()` (lines 182-189)\n4. Token union and caching via `tokenunion.New()` and `tokencache.New()` (lines 191-198)\n5. Bearer token and WebSocket protocol wrapping (line 198)\n6. Request union combining all authenticators via `union.New()` (line 225)\n7. Authenticated group addition via `group.NewAuthenticatedGroupAdder()` (line 227)\n8. Anonymous authentication via `anonymous.NewAuthenticator()` (line 232)\n\n**Bearer Token Authenticator**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go`\nThe `Authenticator` struct (line 32) and its `AuthenticateRequest()` method (lines 42-76) extract bearer tokens from HTTP Authorization headers, delegating to a token authenticator for validation.\n\n**Client Certificate Authenticator**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/x509/x509.go`\nContains two main authenticators:\n- `Authenticator` struct (lines 116-119) that verifies client certificates and converts them to user info via `AuthenticateRequest()` (lines 134-203)\n- `Verifier` struct (lines 206-213) that verifies certificates before delegating to wrapped authenticators\n- `CommonNameUserConversion` (line 276) extracts user identity from certificate Common Name\n\n**Service Account Token Authenticator**: Implemented across three files:\n1. `pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go`: Contains `JWTTokenAuthenticator()` function (line 227) that creates a generic JWT token authenticator for service accounts. The `jwtTokenAuthenticator` type (lines 316-321) implements the `authenticator.Token` interface with `AuthenticateToken()` method (lines 334-412) that validates JWT tokens using public keys and verifies claims.\n\n2. `pkg/serviceaccount/legacy.go`: Contains `NewLegacyValidator()` (line 65) that creates a legacy service account validator. The `legacyValidator` type implements domain-specific validation for legacy service account tokens, checking secret validity and token contents.\n\n3. `pkg/serviceaccount/claims.go`: Contains `NewValidator()` (line 132) that creates the modern service account validator. The `validator` type implements `Validate()` (lines 144-292) to verify token claims and validate referenced resources (service accounts, pods, secrets, nodes).\n\n**Anonymous Authenticator**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/anonymous/anonymous.go`\nThe `Authenticator` struct (lines 32-34) and `NewAuthenticator()` function (lines 55-62) enable anonymous access. The `AuthenticateRequest()` method (lines 36-49) returns an anonymous user when conditions match.\n\n**Supporting Components**:\n- **Token File**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/tokenfile/tokenfile.go` implements static token authentication via `NewCSV()` (lines 45-91)\n- **Token Union**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/union/union.go` combines multiple token authenticators with `New()` and `NewFailOnError()` functions\n- **Request Union**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/union/union.go` combines multiple request authenticators\n- **Token Cache**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/cache/cached_token_authenticator.go` provides caching via `New()` function (lines 97-127)\n- **WebSocket Protocol**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/websocket/protocol.go` enables bearer token authentication over WebSocket\n- **Request Headers**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/headerrequest/requestheader.go` implements front proxy authentication\n- **Authenticated Group**: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/group/authenticated_group_adder.go` adds the system:authenticated group to successful authentications\n\nAll these components work together in the chain orchestrated by `config.go:New()` to provide comprehensive authentication for the Kubernetes API server, supporting multiple authentication mechanisms in a configurable, composable architecture."
